 society; and (3) the relationship of these contributions to the character or nature of life in the United States. The result is a coherent collection of considerable breadth and exceptional quality. The essays include "Time's American Adventures: American History and Historical Writing since 1776" by William Goetzmann; "Economics: Its Direct and Indirect Impact in America, 1776-1976" by Joseph J. Spengler; "Sociology in America: The Experience of Two Centuries" by Robin M. Williams; "Understanding Political Life in America: The Contribution of Political Science" by Heinz Eulau; "Anthropology in America" by Walter Goldschmidt; and "Geography As a Social Science: Recent American Experience" by Kevin Cox.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aSocial scienceszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aSocial sciences--United States--History. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aBonjean, Charles M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBonjean, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCox, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEulau, Heinz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoetzmann, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldschmidt, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLineberry, Robert L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchneider, Louis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchneider, Louis, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSpengler, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilliams, Robin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/77530540uhttps://www.d